 purana\n                  or the other. But the issue is whether they understood\n                  the essence or getting carried away with superficial\n                  details. After all, shastras are not as simple as\n                  1+2=3. There are contradictory guidelines if one just\n                  focuses on the superficial specifics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;div style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:\n                13.3333px;font-family:\n                arial,helvetica,sans-serif;background-color:\n                transparent;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;div style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:\n                13.3333px;font-family:\n                arial,helvetica,sans-serif;background-color:\n                transparent;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For\n                  e.g Adding Om at the beginning or end of a mantra also\n                  has some clauses as to who should and should not do\n                  it. &gt;&lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;div style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:\n                13.3333px;font-family:\n                arial,helvetica,sans-serif;background-color:\n                transparent;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Some shastras actually say that a mantra\n                  without Om at the beginning is like a headless person\n                  and one should add Om in front of EVERY mantra.&lt;br&gt;\n                  &lt;br&gt;\n                  Again, I don&#39;t want to spread another thumbrule by\n                  leaving out the nuance. So let me say a couple of\n                  words on the essence. It is saying that one should\n                  worship any form or energy thinking of Brahman (Om) as\n                  the source and the deity (mantra) as a manifestation\n                  emanating from Brahman.&lt;br&gt;\n                  &lt;br&gt;\n                  Of course, depending on one&#39;s purpose and state, one\n                  need not think of a deity that way. If you take a\n                  mantra like navakshari that starts with &quot;aim&quot;, there\n                  are people who add Om at the beginning and some who\n                  don&#39;t. These 2 mantras work differently, but I don&#39;t\n                  see a &quot;risk&quot; in either.&lt;br&gt;\n                  &lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If one&#39;s guru advises one to\n                  do or not do something, one should follow it. I have\n                  no comments on them. But pravachana kartas can do\n                  better than spreading scare in simple and harmless\n                  issues. It is one thing to say that an atyugra\n                  devata&#39;s mantra should not be done by everyone and\n                  another to say that Om should not be done by everyone.&lt;br&gt;\n                  &lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;/span&gt;Bottomline is that there are several mantras that\n                have very specific energy that may or may not be\n                compatible with someone&#39;s temperament and spiritual\n                trajectory. One may need a guru to guide one. But some\n                mantras (like Shiva panchakshari, Narayana ashtakshari,\n                Vasudeva dwadasakshari) are suitable for all. The same\n                is with Om. It is a simple plain mantra without any\n                specific energies and suitable for all really. The only\n                issue is that it may be better for most people to\n                actually go for something that has specific energies\n                suitable for their spiritual trajectory, than a plan\n                mantra. This is just like a specific deity (Ganesha,\n                Surya, Vishnu, Shiva, Durga etc) being more suitable for\n                most people than nirguNa brahman!&lt;br&gt;\n                &lt;br&gt;\n              &lt;/span&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;\n              &lt;div style=&quot;color:rgb(0, 0,\n                0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean,\n                sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;\n                --------&lt;br&gt;\n                Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a\n                  moz-do-not-send=&quot;true&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;\n                  href=&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;div style=&quot;color:rgb(0, 0,\n                0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean,\n                sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;\n                Â &lt;/div&gt;\n              &lt;div&gt;\n                &lt;blockquote style=&quot;border-left: 2px solid rgb(16, 16,\n                  255);&quot;&gt;\n                  &lt;div style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica,\n                    sans-serif;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;\n                    &lt;div style=&quot;font-family: times new roman, new york,\n                      times, serif;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;\n                      &lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;\n                        &lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span\n                              style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;\n                          Sreenivasa Rao &lt;a class=&quot;moz-txt-link-rfc2396E&quot; href=&quot;mailto:sreenivas_s@...&quot;&gt;&lt;sreenivas_s@...&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n                          &lt;b&gt;&lt;span styl